<div id="Idea_3627"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3627-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3627">Require Web Sites That Provide Greater Explanatory Materials&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6826-4049">bbrandon</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Federal agencies must pay the Federal Register by the page for the length of their rulemaking preambles & rules. Thus a Register NPRM is far from a complete recital of the materials supporting a rulemaking proposal. As a consequence agencies should use the Web to supplement the Register.</div>
